pise me in no time at all &gt;8O). I'm not that good an artist and I'm not that good a writer (though my writing is better than my art) so please bear with me. Here's a little concept I've been tossing around since I drew this one character a few weeks ago. I would post a picture of him but My scanner is broken :O(.<br>
<br>
The Mamba:<br>
<br>
The story centers around Miko Ashanti AKA The Mamba. Miko is a 7', lanky, dreadlocked, former Talon revolutionary. Some looming secret about the Talon Revolution (which was against the government of the Laius system for the right to individual planets to have their own governments) and his ship (also named The Mamba) is ever-present for the duration of the Manga until it is revealed near the end. I'm not going to tell you that sectret now because what would be the point of the whole manga? ;O) <br>
<br>
The story picks up with The Mamba on Nexus, a, pardon my french, @#%$-planet with one giant slum holding its entire population. Its a place run by crime bosses and druglords where escaped convicts, outlaws, and those just plain out of luck go because theres just nowhere else. Miko is getting by by doing hits for one of the major crime families on the planet. <br>
<br>
I'll tell you more when I get home but my class just ended so gotta go! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba2>TheMamba2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/19/02 12:25:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Mamba</span><hr size=1> Ok, ready to wrte some more 8O)<br>
<br>
The story starts with a rather uneventful run of the mill hit on a lower crime boss who's trying to start up his own operation. I figure that this way, I can introduce Miko's intresting style of gunfighting (always jumping and moving and fliping while taking shots sparsely but with extreme accuracy) and cool martial arts style that goes almost untouched in manga and the popular media, Capoera (spelling?) as well as his own personal and primal style. Capoera is a Latin American/African style also known as &quot;fight-dancing&quot; in which you never stop moving and emphasis is on acrobatic dodges and attacks, mostly with the feet. <br>
<br>
In this introductory issue, I can also show his feelings about his work and his general outlook on life, which is it's useless and he wishes it were better but he doesn't know how to make it better. <br>
<br>
Well that's about it. I'll get some pencils posted of him as soon as I can get to a scanner and some inks as soon as I can get to a light table. <br>
<br>
GIMME SOME FEEDBACK!!!<br>
<br>
<br>
PS<br>
<br>
You will also see The Mamba around the forum because I signed up for this forum here and at home because of some wierdness with my school's network. <br>
