Or was it &quot;For a Few Dollars More&quot;? Can't keep those Eastwood spaghetti westerns straight.<br>
<br>
Anyways, how did the Mamba get such an outlook on life? Just born a sociopath, or was it the upbringing? Perhaps a tragic event in the past?<br>
<br>
These aren't things that you have to reveal right away, but that you should have decided. He sounds like a man dictated by his philosophy, so you draw up a little timeline for him. Get some ideas about how he got involved in the revolution, what happened then, why is he where he is now, etc... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba>The Mamba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fresh Meat</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/19/02 4:03:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Mamba</span><hr size=1> I've got all those ideas now but that's all part of the big looming secret so I can't really reveal all that. I will say that it has something to do with his family and past friends/lovers. I think its one of my better basic plots to date but you can judge for yourself soon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uselenesama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>selene sama</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/19/02 7:19:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Mamba</span><hr size=1> Hmmmmmss... sounds interesting. <br>
   I think it was a wise idea to go with a more african approach to your character. there are very few actual dreadlocked type hair styles and few honest darker characters. It's very original and about time ^_~. I am assuming that he is black , though that doesn't really have to be the case. It would be awesome if he was because ( and I admit my knowlegde is really limited) all you see in anime/manga styles is the token black guy role. I can't wait to see a posting of him. Good luck on your story ^_^  <p>" Can't fight the moon light" Tis I, Selene!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba2>TheMamba2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/20/02 5:20:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Mamba</span><hr size=1> Actually, I've NEVER seen dreadlocks drawn in the manga style, which is sort of understandable considering the dreadlocked population of Japan ^_^. Because of that, I really had no examples to copy from so his hair is a bit of difficulty but I'm satisfied with it for now and I'll probably develop it more as I go along. The Mamba is black and so am I and I think its really annoying  that there are token black people in not just manga but every form of visual entertainment. I'd much prefer that you just leave them out because you know that they're there just because their black and not because they add anything to a story. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uselenesama.showPublicProfile?language=EN>selene sama</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/20/02 4:32:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Mamba</span><hr size=1>  More power to you! <br>
    Your story is going to be great because you have a connection to the character. I hate it when people try to write stories with characters they don't really feel for or even relate too. lol ... explains why my characters always come off as a little ditzy and at some point can really be bitchy ^_~. <br>
By the way, should have known by your name that you were African American , Teehee. The Black Mamba, most deadly and feared snake in africa, good choice. <p>" Can't fight the moon light" Tis I, Selene!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba>The Mamba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/20/02 6:57:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Mamba</span><hr size=1> Yep. Miko is basically the kind of guy who strikes sparsley but is very deadly when he does so I knew it would be a snake and the mamba is extremely deadly feared and... well black <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=themamba>The Mamba</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(3/20/02 7:04:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=567.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Mamba</span><hr size=1> Oh, one more thing. I posted some of my concept pencilings in the art in progress section so you can see the bugger if you'd like. <p>I am the Insular Dotard
